Shufro, Rose & Co.Investing, protecting and building the wealth of our clients since 1938.Our People
Portfolio Managers:
EDWARD G. SHUFROEdward G. Shufro received his B.A. from Yale College in 1955 and his M.B.A. from Harvard in 1958. He joined the firm in 1958, became a Principal in 1965, and is a Senior Managing Director. His father, Salwyn Shufro (1905-2001), was a co-founder of SRC.
STEPHEN LEITStephen Leit received his B.A. from the University of Rochester in 1967 and his M.A. from Northwestern University in 1970. He became a Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) in 1978, joined the firm in 1984, and became a Principal in 1989. He is a Senior Managing Director.
STEVEN J. GLASSSteven J. Glass received his B.S. in Finance from the University of Hartford in 1988 and joined the firm the same year. He became a Principal in 1997 and is a Senior Managing Director.
HARVEY WACHT Harvey Wacht received his B.B.A. from Baruch College in 1967. He became a Certified Public Accountant (CPA) in 1972 and was a Principal at Herzog Heine Geduld for thirty years in senior executive and investment positions. Mr. Wacht joined the firm in 2001 and became a Principal and Senior Managing Director in 2003.
JOHN M. CONTANTJohn M. Contant received his B.S. in Finance from Lehigh University in 1996 and joined the firm the same year. He became a Principal and Senior Managing Director in 2004.
GREGORY D. SHUFROGregory D. Shufro received his B.A. in English from the University of Pennsylvania in 1991 and his J.D. from Fordham University School of Law in 1997. Prior to joining the firm in 2003, he practiced law specializing in securities litigation and bankruptcy. He became a Principal and Senior Managing Director in 2008. His father, Edward Shufro, has been a Principal of the firm since 1965.

Greg is the recipient of the 2012 Impact Award from the Child Center of NY for innovation in business and service to disadvantaged children. Greg currently serves as Vice President of the Board of the Child Center of NY. He also serves on the Advisory Board of the Roosevelt House Public Policy Institute at Hunter College and on the Board of Trustees of the Jewish Center of the Hamptons.
TONIA L. KAMINSKYTonia L. Kaminsky received her B.S. in Business Administration from the University of Massachusetts in 1991 and joined the firm in 1999. She became a Principal and Senior Managing Director in 2009.
BARBARA P. SILVERMANBarbara P. Silverman received her B.A. from Dartmouth College in 1989 and her M.A. from the University of Michigan in 1991. She became a Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) in 1999 and was a vice president at Arnhold and S. Bleichroeder and a Principal at Rosenblum Silverman Sutton, a registered investment adviser. She joined the firm in 2006 and is an Executive Managing Director.
Client Relationship Managers:
STEPHANIE CARCHIAStephanie received her B.S. in Marketing from the Smeal College of Business at The Pennsylvania State University. She joined the firm in 2015.
BRITTANY MALTBYBrittany received her B.S. in Architecture from the University of Virginia. She joined the firm in 2016.
